this is a collection of externals made with Faust Programming Language (http://faust.grame.fr/). the three exernals are the units that are part of a compressor (level measuration/static curve/smoother - the names that I used are respectively: "level" - "staticcurve" - "inseguitore"). in these way it's possible to use them to build a compressor of course, but also you can use them individually and/or use them in a different way.

in the folder there's also a paper from BBC Research "G.W. McNally - dynamic range control of digital audio signals"; it could be useful to understand what is the work of each unit.

the file ".dsp" are the source files in Faust and can be used to compile the object for different OS and different programming language and/or environment.
